her the callout view should be dismissed automatically"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when the map view’s viewport changes. Note that a single tap on the map view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"still dismisses the callout view regardless of the value of this property."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The callout view will be dismissed if this optional property is unimplemented."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncalloutview\/dismissesautomatically","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCalloutView\/dismissesAutomatically","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","kind":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate